			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Dropcam (http://www.dropcam.com) is making the next great consumer gadget - a user-centric web-connected video camera you watch from anywhere.&nbsp; Use your smartphone to check in on your baby, pets, home, or small business.</p>
<p>
It sounds easy, but making a stable, highly available media streaming system that&#39;s easy enough for mom and dad to use is hard.</p>
<p>
If you&#39;re up for interesting problems at a startup building a real mass-market product, we&rsquo;d love your help developing a proud, user-focused engineering culture and fulfilling our mission: watch anywhere from anywhere.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Design and maintain the backend software that powers the Dropcam platform</li>
<li>
Design and maintain tools to help manage Dropcam servers</li>
<li>
Maintain and provision servers</li>
<li>
Investigate bugs and diagnose issues</li>
<li>
Share your knowledge with the team by conducting design and code reviews</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Fluent in Python and C</li>
<li>
Extensive knowledge of networking protocols and technologies (SSL, etc.)</li>
<li>
Extensive experience developing networked applications&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Knowledge of Linux systems and POSIX</li>
<li>
Experience working with very large amounts of data and scalable systems</li>
<li>
Experience with database systems (PostgreSQL preferred)</li>
<li>
A degree in computer science or related technical discipline, or the equivalent</li>
<li>
Strong communication and documentation skills</li>
<li>
Downtime makes you cry</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Nice to Have</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Good working knowledge of media codecs and technologies (H.264, AAC, etc.)</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>About Dropcam</strong></p>
<p>
Dropcam (http://www.dropcam.com) is a venture-backed San Francisco startup building a consumer-focused, web-connected internet camera focused on the home monitoring market.&nbsp; Our goal is to help you watch the things you love from anywhere in the world and make sure they&rsquo;re safe and sound.</p>
<p>
The company&#39;s first product, Dropcam HD, was announced at CES 2012 to rave reviews and media coverage.&nbsp; The Dropcam HD pairs with an online service that provides cloud-based recording and alert notifications.&nbsp; Users watch video of their children from work, their homes and cars while on vacation, and their businesses when relaxing over the weekend.</p>
<p>
Dropcam offers a long list of benefits, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>
competitive base salaries</li>
<li>
pre-IPO stock options</li>
<li>
medical and dental benefits</li>
<li>
breakfast and catered lunch daily</li>
<li>
an amazing 17th floor view overlooking San Francisco</li>
<li>
your favorite flavor of Keurig K-cups for coffee</li>
<li>
really nice folks building a company to be proud of</li>
</ul>
<p>
We&rsquo;re a small team developing the next great consumer gadget &ndash; join us in making it a reality!</p>
