			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Dropcam (http://www.dropcam.com) is making the next great consumer gadget - a user-centric web-connected video camera you watch from anywhere. Use your smartphone to check in on your baby, pets, home, or small business.</p>
<p>
It sounds easy, but making a stable, highly available media streaming system that&#39;s easy enough for mom and dad to use is hard.</p>
<p>
We&#39;re funded by Accel Partners, Menlo Ventures, Kapor Capital, and Felicis Ventures, who have backed early-stage companies like Facebook, Groupon, and Mint. &nbsp;Dropcam&#39;s offices are located in San Francisco, CA.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
Do you love the idea of helping to build a world-class engineering team?</p>
<p>
Are you constantly amazed by your own sourcing abilities and how you can quickly find good candidates with software experience?</p>
<p>
Do you have a good BS detector when speaking about technical projects and a candidate&#39;s responsibilities?</p>
<p>
You will be responsible for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
creating detailed job descriptions while working with the engineering team to determine key criteria</li>
<li>
sourcing candidates and creatively finding the best fits for each role</li>
<li>
screening for folks who are college interns to new graduate hires to experienced developers</li>
<li>
preparing the hiring team for interviews and collecting feedback</li>
<li>
guiding candidates through the process, from introduction through accepting the offer</li>
<li>
helping to build Dropcam&#39;s culture and ensuring the people here are happy, friendly, and folks you love to work with</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
experience in full life cycle recruiting at a fast paced technology company</li>
<li>
